Additional musicians who recorded parts for ''Chinese Democracy'' but are unlikely to feature:
*[[Brian May]] - guitar
*[[Shaquille O'Neal]] - vocals

==Title conflicts==
On [[April 1]], [[2003]] ([[April Fool's Day]]), [[The Offspring]] announced that they would be naming their upcoming album ''Chinese Democrazy (You Snooze, You Lose)''. The Offspring lead singer [[Dexter Holland]] elaborated, "You snooze, you lose. Axl ripped off my braids, I ripped off his album title."<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1470891/20030401/story.jhtml | title = Guns N' Roses' ''Chinese Democracy'' Snatched By Offspring | accessdate = 2007-01-08 | last = D'Angelo | first = Joe | date = 2003-04-01 | work = MTV.com}}</ref> However, the Offspring album was eventually released under the title ''[[Splinter (album)|Splinter]]'' instead.

In early 2005, [[Nosferatu (band)|Nosferatu]] announced ''Chinese Democracy'' as the working title of their fifth studio album, but in October the same year, the band's website announced that the title had to be changed after a threat of legal action from Axl Rose's attorneys. The working title was then changed to ''The Long Lost Weekend'', and it remains undecided which title the band will use.

